page.title: 07ECOLOGY
page.content: In this area the main concentration of natural vegetation is along roadside verges as the remainder of the land has been intensively cultivated by man.Apart from rough grass there is a multitude of common wildflowers.During the month of May the roadside verges are a proliferation of colour. Numerous plants contribute to this including{Dandelion, Gorse, Daisy}and {Groundsol.}In addition to this basic grondcover small pockets of{Vetches, {Thistles, Wild Roses}and{Foxgloves were identified.Numerous varieties of trees act as part boundaries between cultivated fields.The most common deciduous species are{Beech, Horse {Chestnut, Sycamore}and the coniferous varieties include{Scots Pine, Larch and{Norwegian Spruce.
